r `spring-test` and ensure I have everything needed on the classpath, especially `spring-aop` and method security classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing method security tests**\\n\\nI’m working on implementing a configuration for method security using `@EnableMethodSecurity(prePostEnabled = true)`. I’ve set up a `MessageService` class with a `readMessage` method that checks for the authority to read messages. For testing, I’ll create an `AnnotationConfigApplicationContext` for the configuration. \\n\\nAfter clearing the security context, I’m testing if an exception is thrown when accessing the message without proper authentication. Then I’ll set up an authenticated user and check if it can read the message correctly. I also need to confirm if `EnableMethodSecurity` is available in version 5.7.11 using `javap`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hEEaoH2dVmNpgIZTRhkRrJeB|fc_0a8581cb5ddac578016a02556d9bd0819d9691deb5d4b50a79", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.springframework.security/spring-security-config/5.7.11/build/jacoco/effective -path '*EnableMethodSecurity.class' -print"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 235, "output": 441, "cacheRead": 15360, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16036, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778537826520, "responseId": "resp_0a8581cb5ddac578016a0255633cb8819d82d8f44aa43d0943"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_hEEaoH2dVmNpgIZTRhkRrJeB|fc_0a8581cb5ddac578016a02556d9bd0819d9691deb5d4b50a79", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.springframework.security/spring-security-config/5.7.11/build/jacoco/effective/spring_security_config_5_7_11_jar/org/springframework/security/config/annotation/method/configuration/EnableMethodSecurity.class\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778537837933}]